# Implementation Plan V2: Model-Specific DSPy Strategy & Evaluation Hardening

## Goal

Complete all remaining work items from the confirmed methodology. The two critical gaps identified from the deep codebase review are:

1. **DSPy Signatures have no model-specific tricks yet** — the implementation plan explicitly called for a Strategy Pattern with per-model optimizations, but the current [signatures.py](file:///C:/VIRAK/Python%20Code/aero-guardian/src/llm/signatures.py) uses only universal rules.
2. **RFlyMAD validation thresholds are not statistically grounded** — [methodology_enhancement_plan.md](file:///C:/Users/User/.gemini/antigravity/brain/23212d1f-8f58-4197-97cd-12b317768cd9/methodology_enhancement_plan.md) confirmed we must derive thresholds from 3-sigma (Z-score) bounds of the ALFA normal flight distribution, not arbitrary constants.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Model-Specific Tricks vs Universal: Which is better?**
> 
> **Answer: Model-specific tricks are superior**, and here is the engineering proof:
> 
> | | Universal Only | Model-Specific |
> |---|---|---|
> | Claude XML `<thinking>` blocks | Not used | Exploits Claude's native XML reasoning |
> | OpenAI `response_format: json` | Not used | Strict JSON mode eliminates parse errors |
> | Claude negative constraints | Generic "do not" | `<forbidden>` XML blocks Claude respects deeply |
> | OpenAI system role strictness | Shared docstring | Dedicated system prompt with function-call style |
> | DSPy compatibility | Works everywhere | Works everywhere (tricks are additive, not breaking) |
> 
> **The design: Both approaches coexist.** A universal base signature provides the safety net (works with any model). Model-specific "prompt enhancers" are injected at runtime when the provider is detected. If you switch to a new model (e.g., Gemini), it falls back to universal automatically.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Model-Specific DSPy Prompt Enhancers (NEW)

#### [NEW] [prompt_enhancers.py](file:///C:/VIRAK/Python%20Code/aero-guardian/src/llm/prompt_enhancers.py)

A new module implementing the Strategy Pattern for model-specific DSPy prompt optimization.

- **`BasePromptEnhancer`**: Abstract base class with `enhance_scenario_prompt()` and `enhance_report_prompt()`.
- **`AnthropicEnhancer`**: Injects Claude-optimized tricks:
  - `<thinking>` XML blocks for chain-of-thought reasoning
  - `<forbidden>` XML blocks listing prohibited outputs (hallucination guard)
  - `<output_rules>` XML blocks enforcing ENUM validation
  - Negative constraint lists ("You must NEVER output...")
- **`OpenAIEnhancer`**: Injects OpenAI-optimized tricks:
  - System-role strictness preamble
  - `response_format: { type: "json_object" }` hint in prompt
  - Few-shot exemplar formatting optimized for GPT tokenizer
  - Function-call style output schema enforcement
- **`get_enhancer(provider: str)`**: Factory function that returns the correct enhancer based on `LLM_PROVIDER` env var. Falls back to `BasePromptEnhancer` (universal/no-op) for unknown providers.

